22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdiane-von-furstenberg-impact-of-wrap-dress-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDiane%20von%20Furstenberg%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20faked%20it%20till%20I%20made%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20a%20Stanford%20Business%20School%20audience%20in%202024%2C%20recalling%20that%20she%20pretended%20to%20be%20an%20intern%20when%20her%20company%20was%20a%20one-woman%20affair%20to%20drum%20up%20interest%20and%20used%20made-up%20names%20when%20communicating%20with%20partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Business%20Insider%20investigation%20into%20Pierson's%20enterprise%20reveals%20that%20pretending%20to%20be%20her%20own%20intern%20may%20not%20have%20been%20her%20only%20distortion%20of%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20review%20of%20internal%20documents%20and%20dashboards%2C%20recordings%20of%20meetings%2C%20and%20interviews%20with%20more%20than%2010%20company%20insiders%20uncovered%20questions%20about%20what%20Pierson%20has%20told%20the%20public%20and%20advertisers%20about%20her%20business%20when%20compared%20with%20what%20her%20own%20records%20show%20%E2%80%94%20including%20how%20many%20subscribers%20her%20newsletter%20has.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Pierson%20confirmed%20to%20Business%20Insider%20that%20The%20Newsette's%20daily%20newsletter%20goes%20out%20to%20about%20500%2C000%20subscribers%20each%20day.%20That's%20less%20than%20half%20the%201.3%20million%20subscribers%20claimed%20in%20a%202025%20pitch%20deck%20to%20advertisers%20and%20the%20million-plus%20referenced%20by%20Pierson%20in%20multiple%20public%20appearances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20the%20larger%20figure%20reflects%20the%20company's%20overall%20email%20list%2C%20which%20includes%20what%20they%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bdisengaged%20subscribers%26quot%3B%20who%20have%20been%20%26quot%3Bfunneled%20out%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20daily%20newsletter%20by%20a%20quality%20control%20mechanism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20sent%20to%20Business%20Insider%20and%20posted%20on%20Instagram%2C%20Pierson%20called%20criticism%20of%20her%20business%20a%20%26quot%3Bsmear%20campaign%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20claims%20involve%20%26quot%3Bfalse%20statements%20and%20fabricated%20information%26quot%3B%20meant%20to%20hamper%20her%20ability%20to%20continue%20supporting%20women%20through%20her%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20messed%20with%20the%20wrong%20person%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPierson%20has%20touted%20The%20Newsette%20Media%20Group's%202021%20revenue%20%E2%80%94%20%2440%20million%2C%20according%20to%20both%20Pierson%20and%20former%20employees%20%E2%80%94%20in%20public%20appearances%20as%20recently%20as%20last%20year.%20She's%20never%20publicly%20revealed%20revenue%20figures%20for%20subsequent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompany%20documents%20seen%20by%20Business%20Insider%20paint%20a%20less%20rosy%20picture%20for%20last%20year%3A%20The%20company's%202024%20revenue%20goal%20was%20%245%20million.%20The%20Pierson%20spokesperson%20said%20this%20number%20was%20not%20accurate%20but%20declined%20to%20provide%20further%20information.%20They%20added%20that%20the%20company%20is%20currently%20profitable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20revenue%20decline%20can%20be%20attributed%20to%20the%202023%20shuttering%20of%20Newland%2C%20the%20creative%20agency%20that%20Pierson%20launched%20in%20late%202020%20as%20part%20of%20The%20Newsette%20Media%20Group.%20She%20said%20Newland%20drove%20more%20revenue%20than%20the%20newsletter%20business%20itself%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Newsette%20Media%20Group%20now%20employs%20eight%20people%2C%20down%20from%2040%20at%20its%20peak%2C%20the%20Pierson%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPierson's%20business%2C%20by%20multiple%20measures%2C%20has%20fallen%20from%20its%20heights.%20It's%20a%20problem%20she's%20familiar%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3Dv4YhWcmbj3Q%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%202024%20TEDx%20Talk%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Pierson%20spoke%20about%20%26quot%3Ball%20of%20the%20billionaire%20guys%26quot%3B%20who%20had%20raised%20capital%20and%20whose%20companies%20were%20now%20%26quot%3Bworth%20zero.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20don't%20realize%2C%20you%20have%20%241%20billion%20on%20paper%2C%20that%20paper%20can%20burn%20real%20fast%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20Pierson%20has%20perfected%20her%20founder%20narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20identical%20twin%2C%20Pierson%20struggled%20in%20school%20and%20was%20labeled%2C%20in%20her%20own%20telling%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20dumb%20twin.%26quot%3B%20When%20she%20got%20to%20Boston%20University%2C%20she%20said%20in%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emultiple%20podcast%20interviews%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eshe%20floundered%20in%20school%2C%20uninspired%20by%20learning%20about%20the%20Earth's%20crust%20and%20how%20to%20properly%20measure%20the%20area%20of%20a%20triangle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20decided%20to%20focus%20on%20what%20she%20did%20like%20%E2%80%94%20magazines%20%E2%80%94%20and%20founded%20The%20Newsette%20as%20a%20newsletter%20during%20her%20sophomore%20year%20at%20the%20age%20of%2019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20morning%2C%20she'd%20wake%20up%20at%205%20a.m.%20and%20spend%20five%20hours%20drafting%20a%20newsletter%20for%20her%20subscribers.%20During%20class%2C%20she%20DM-ed%20people%20on%20Facebook%2C%20telling%20them%20that%20if%20they%20brought%20on%20new%20subscribers%2C%20they%20could%20add%20%26quot%3BNewsette%20ambassador%26quot%3B%20to%20their%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20started%20in%202015%2C%20there%20weren't%20any%20newsletters%20out%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20she'd%20later%20tell%20the%20audience%20at%20Stanford.%20(Prominent%20launches%20of%20newsletters%20with%20a%20similar%20flair%20included%20The%20Skimm%20in%202012%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgwyneth-paltrow-goop-layoffs-restructuring-pivots-struggling-celebrity-brand-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGwyneth%20Paltrow's%20Goop%20in%202008%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20she%20graduated%20and%20had%20hammered%20out%20the%20product%20details%2C%20she%20couldn't%20find%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20she%20took%20a%20%2415%2C000%20loan%20from%20her%20parents.%20She's%20said%20she%20has%20since%20repaid%20the%20loan%20and%20has%20posted%20on%20Instagram%20that%20she%20%26quot%3Bmade%20her%20mom%20a%20millionaire%26quot%3B%20by%20giving%20her%20a%20stake%20in%20Newsette%20Media%20Group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20venture%20backing%2C%20she%20had%20to%20be%20profitable%20right%20away%2C%20she%20said%2C%20so%20she%20began%20selling%20ads%2C%20making%20%2425%2C000%20in%20her%20first%20month%20of%20accepting%20advertisers%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPierson%20was%20successful%20in%20attracting%20press%20attention%2C%20at%20first%20from%20small%20college-targeted%20outlets%20and%20her%20hometown%20station%2C%20later%20from%20outlets%20including%20Elle%2C%20WWD%2C%20and%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20interviews%20were%20peppered%20with%20her%20catch-phrases%3A%20The%20Newsette%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bgift%20in%20your%20inbox%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20often%20said%2C%20and%20at%20the%20beginning%2C%20she%20had%20three%20employees%2C%20%26quot%3Bme%2C%20myself%2C%20and%20I.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20a%20meeting%20with%20von%20Furstenberg%2C%20whom%20Pierson%20calls%20her%20fairy%20godmother%2C%20resulted%20in%20a%20partnership%20with%20the%20fashion%20designer%3A%20a%20publication%20called%20the%20Weekly%20Wrap%2C%20which%20Pierson%20said%20on%20the%20%26quot%3BMoney%20Rehab%26quot%3B%20podcast%20was%20one%20of%20her%20big%20breaks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%20December%202019%2C%20she%20appeared%20on%20Forbes'%2030%20Under%2030%20list%2C%20saying%20The%20Newsette%20had%20grown%20to%20500%2C000%20subscribers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERevenue%2C%20Pierson%20said%20in%20a%20number%20of%20interviews%2C%20shot%20from%20%241%20million%20in%202019%20to%20%247%20million%20in%202020%20to%20%2440%20million%20%E2%80%94%20%2410%20million%20of%20it%20profit%20%E2%80%94%20in%202021.%20She%20said%20that%20revenue%20and%20the%20company's%20500%2C000-plus%20subscribers%20allowed%20her%20to%20sell%20a%201.25%25%20stake%20in%20the%20company%20at%20a%20%24200%20million%20valuation.%20The%20Pierson%20spokesperson%20declined%20to%20say%20who%20the%20investor%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20The%20Newsette%20Media%20Group's%20valuation%20and%20her%20stake%20in%20Wondermind%2C%20a%20mental-health%20startup%20she%20had%20cofounded%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frare-beauty-sale-could-make-selena-gomez-billionaire-net-worth-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESelena%20Gomez%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20Gomez's%20mom%2C%20Forbes%20reported%20she%20was%20worth%20%24220%20million%20in%20August%202022.%20That%20made%20her%20the%20youngest%2C%20wealthiest%20self-made%20BIPOC%20woman%20in%20America%2C%20according%20to%20the%20magazine%2C%20a%20title%20she%20repeats%20with%20gusto.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225178%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Daniella%20Pierson%20with%20poet%20Rupi%20Kaur%20and%20Parade%20founder%20Cami%20T%C3%A9llez%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68942666f748d8c055f7091e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223452%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDaniella%20Pierson%20with%20poet%20Rupi%20Kaur%2C%20left%2C%20and%20Parade%20founder%20Cami%20T%C3%A9llez%2C%20right%2C%20at%20the%202023%20TIME%20Women%20of%20the%20Year%20event.%3Cp%3EKevin%20Mazur%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20TIME%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20examination%20of%20company%20documents%20shows%20a%20growing%20gap%20between%20the%20subscriber%20numbers%20Pierson%20gave%20publicly%20and%20what%20was%20on%20the%20books.%20On%20August%2010%2C%202022%2C%20the%20day%20the%20Forbes%20story%20came%20out%20touting%20more%20than%20half%20a%20million%20subscribers%2C%20The%20Newsette%20had%20411%2C000%2C%20according%20to%20documentation%20reviewed%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202023%20interview%20with%20Forbes%2C%20she%20said%20it%20was%20on%20track%20to%20reach%201%20million%20subscribers%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year.%20According%20to%20company%20documentation%2C%20The%20Newsette%20had%20no%20more%20than%20570%2C000%20subscribers%20that%20year.%20At%20the%202024%20Stanford%20talk%2C%20she%20said%20she%20had%20hit%20the%201%20million%20mark%3B%20the%20records%20say%20The%20Newsette%20had%20fallen%20below%20500%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20repeated%20those%20numbers%20to%20advertisers.%20A%20pitch%20deck%20used%20earlier%20this%20year%20claims%20that%20The%20Newsette%20has%20%26quot%3B1.3%20million%2B%20subscribers%26quot%3B%20who%20receive%20its%20weekday%2C%20Saturday%2C%20and%20Sunday%20editions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Pierson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20there%20are%201.2%20million%20emails%20in%20the%20company's%20total%20contact%20list%20%E2%80%94%20including%20people%20who%20no%20longer%20receive%20the%20newsletter%20regularly%20%E2%80%94%20and%20said%20the%20daily%20edition%20currently%20goes%20out%20to%20about%20500%2C000%20active%20subscribers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJacob%20Donnelly%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20A%20Media%20Operator%2C%20a%20newsletter-based%20publication%20for%20people%20building%20digital%20media%20companies%2C%20said%20that%20standard%20industry%20practice%20is%20that%20the%20number%20of%20subscriptions%20refers%20to%20the%20number%20of%20people%20who%20receive%20the%20newsletter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%20were%20to%20go%20out%20and%20say%20I%20have%201.3%20million%20subscribers%2C%20what%20I'm%20saying%20to%20the%20advertiser%20is%20when%20I%20hit%20send%2C%20it's%20going%20out%20to%201.3%20million%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20speaking%20generally%20and%20not%20about%20The%20Newsette%20specifically.%20%26quot%3BIf%20someone%20is%20not%20subscribed%20to%20a%20product%2C%20I%20don't%20see%20how%20they%20could%20be%20classified%20as%20a%20subscriber.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20meeting%20with%20a%20potential%20advertiser%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20a%20recording%20of%20which%20Business%20Insider%20reviewed%2C%20Pierson%20mentioned%20a%20subscriber%20count%20of%20%26quot%3Ba%20million%26quot%3B%20and%20boasted%20that%20%26quot%3Bevery%20single%20day%2C%20our%20sponsors%20get%20at%20least%20250%2C000%20unique%20views.%26quot%3B%20In%20the%20more%20than%20two%20years%20of%20newsletter%20data%20that%20Business%20Insider%20reviewed%2C%20The%20Newsette's%20newsletter%20only%20hit%20that%20many%20unique%20opens%20one%20time.%20More%20than%20half%20of%20the%20days%2C%20it%20had%20fewer%20than%20200%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22DVF%20and%20Daniella%20Pierson%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689419e0194a2d49b8ae228f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222399%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDaniella%20Pierson%20says%20Diane%20von%20Furstenberg%20is%20one%20of%20her%20mentors%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20provided%20her%20with%20her%20big%20break.%3Cp%3EMonica%20Schipper%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20Diane%20von%20Furstenberg%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%202020%2C%20von%20Furstenberg%20personally%20pitched%20Pierson%20to%20Amazon's%20Jeff%20Bezos%2C%20Pierson%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-daniella-pierson-built-the-newsette-wondermind-selena-gomez-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20tech%20giant%20soon%20became%20one%20of%20the%20first%20clients%20of%20Newland%2C%20a%20creative%20agency%20that%20became%2C%20for%20a%20short%20time%2C%20The%20Newsette%20Media%20Group's%20cash%20cow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%20and%20into%202022%2C%20Newland%20completed%20a%20number%20of%20projects%20for%20Amazon%3B%20Pierson%20told%20the%20Stanford%20audience%20that%20the%20company%20%26quot%3Bwas%20responsible%20for%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20revenue.%26quot%3B%20The%20agency%20took%20a%20360-degree%20approach%20to%20social%20media%20marketing%2C%20coming%20up%20with%20the%20brief%2C%20hiring%20the%20talent%2C%20and%20handling%20the%20paid%20media.%20Campaigns%20included%20a%20viral%20Prime%20Day%20TikTok%20push%20featuring%20Snoop%20Dogg%20and%20a%20number%20of%20creators%2C%20and%20content%20for%20Women's%20History%20Month%20with%20Keke%20Palmer%2C%20Mindy%20Kaling%2C%20and%20von%20Furstenberg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20two%20former%20employees%20familiar%20with%20the%20financials%2C%20the%20%2440%20million%20revenue%20figure%20Pierson%20touted%20represented%20gross%20revenue%2C%20or%20all%20of%20the%20money%20that%20flowed%20through%20the%20company%2C%20inclusive%20of%20cash%20reserved%20for%20talent%20and%20paid%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20publicly%20owned%20ad%20agencies%20report%20net%20revenue%20%E2%80%94%20the%20money%20left%20over%20once%20a%20campaign%20is%20finished%20%E2%80%94%20and%20not%20gross%20revenue%2C%20which%20includes%20money%20the%20agency%20gets%20to%20pay%20for%20things%20like%20celebrity%20endorsements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-andy-jassy-note-layoffs-will-extend-into-2023-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAmazon%20underwent%20a%20reorganization%3C%2Fa%3E%20toward%20the%20end%20of%202022%20and%20into%202023%2C%20the%20company%20largely%20paused%20its%20new%20work%20with%20Newland%2C%20according%20to%20four%20former%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20declined%20to%20comment%20to%20Business%20Insider%20about%20its%20business%20with%20Newland.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Amazon's%20departure%2C%20Pierson%20struggled%20to%20bring%20new%20clients%20to%20the%20agency%2C%20said%20four%20former%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENewland%2C%20Pierson%20said%2C%20grew%20to%20eventually%20employ%20the%20majority%20of%20Newsette%20Media%20Group's%20employees.%20In%20December%202022%2C%20Newsette%20conducted%20one%20of%20several%20rounds%20of%20layoffs.%20Former%20employees%20said%20the%20layoffs%20were%20due%20to%20a%20cash%20crunch.%20By%20the%20end%20of%202023%2C%20Newland%20had%20completely%20folded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pierson%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20job%20cuts%20were%20not%20due%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bfinancial%20crunch%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20were%20made%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20%26quot%3Befficiencies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%202024%2C%20the%20company's%20revenue%20goal%20was%20a%20modest%20%245%20million%2C%20according%20to%20internal%20documents.%20The%20Pierson%20spokesperson%20said%20those%20numbers%20were%20not%20accurate%2C%20but%20declined%20to%20provide%20additional%20numbers%20or%20documentation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223390%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Daniella%20Pierson%2C%20Sara%20Blakely%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689423ab3d5881a51c1ec1cf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222543%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESara%20Blakely%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Spanx%2C%20is%20involved%20in%20Daniella%20Pierson's%20latest%20venture%2C%20Chasm%2C%20a%20membership%20club%20that%20aims%20to%20%26quot%3Bclose%20the%20gender%20gap%20through%20entrepreneurship.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ENoam%20Galai%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20TIME%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20Newsette%20Media%20Group%2C%20Pierson%20has%20been%20involved%20in%20other%20ventures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20she%20was%20announced%20as%20the%20co-CEO%20of%20Wondermind%2C%20a%20mental%20health%20website%20that%20she%20cofounded%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-billionaire-selena-gomez-makes-spends-her-fortune-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewith%20Selena%20Gomez%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20singer's%20mother%2C%20Mandy%20Teefey.%20In%202023%2C%20she%20quietly%20left%20the%20company%3B%20the%20circumstances%20of%20her%20departure%20have%20not%20been%20disclosed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20press%20release%20about%20Pierson's%20investment%20in%20a%20group%20attempting%20to%20purchase%20Forbes%20went%20out%2C%20she%20posted%20on%20X%20that%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bon%20the%20board%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20magazine.%20The%20deal%20ended%20up%20falling%20through%2C%20and%20she%20was%20never%20on%20any%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20most%20recent%20venture%20launched%20in%20May.%20Chasm%20is%20a%20%2425%2C000-a-year%20membership%20club%20that%20aims%20to%20%26quot%3Bclose%20the%20gender%20gap%20through%20entrepreneurship.%26quot%3B%20The%20club%20says%20its%20members%20include%20singer%20Lionel%20Richie%20and%20Spanx's%20Sara%20Blakely%2C%20neither%20of%20whom%20responded%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%20Membership%20fees%20will%20fund%20a%20website%20and%20award%20monthly%20five-figure%20grants%20to%20entrepreneurs%2C%20the%20first%20of%20which%20was%20announced%20on%20August%206.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20being%20contacted%20for%20comment%2C%20Pierson%20sent%20a%20statement%20and%20posted%20it%20to%20Instagram%2C%20saying%20there%20was%20a%20coordinated%20attempt%20by%20people%20%26quot%3Bwho%20represent%20everything%20that%20my%20gender%20equality%20initiatives%20have%20fought%20to%20change%26quot%3B%20had%20launched%20a%20%26quot%3Bsmear%20campaign%26quot%3B%20against%20her%20and%20her%20companies%2C%20resulting%20in%20%26quot%3Bfalse%20statements%20and%20fabricated%20information%26quot%3B%20aimed%20at%20eliminating%20her%20ability%20to%20%26quot%3Bcontinue%20to%20put%20millions%20of%20my%20own%20dollars%20into%20helping%20women.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20false%20statements%20don't%20just%20affect%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThey%20affect%20